{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"fields":{"description":"Encode the agent-build invariants that guard against silently-disabled safeguards as tests plus a one-time construction check ŌĆö not per-call runtime blocking. Every mechanism below is a CONCRETE, verified pydantic-ai 1.107.0 signal.\n\n## Why\nSeveral dangerous silent failures are static properties of rebar's OWN agent construction, not per-call events: tools silently stripped when a hook returns None (#5177), tools silently ignored on a non-tool-calling provider (#6186), `usage_limits` silently ignored if set on the `Agent(...)` constructor instead of `run*` (#1987), and usage silently zeroed on some provider adapters (#5360). Asserting these per-call wastes work and risks false-blocking a healthy run ŌĆö they belong in tests + a one-time check.\n\n## What (concrete mechanisms)\n- **Construction-time provider tool-calling check.** VERIFIED signal: a pydantic-ai model exposes `model.profile.supports_tools` (a bool). The check applies where rebar constructs an explicit model OBJECT (the anthropic path via `_build_retrying_anthropic_model`, the primary path in practice). Guard: FOR A TOOL-USING op (`tools` non-empty) where `model` is a model OBJECT exposing `.profile` (`not isinstance(model, str)` and `hasattr(model.profile, 'supports_tools')`), assert `model.profile.supports_tools is True`; else raise `LLMConfigError` (fail fast). It is a NO-OP for the string-model paths (OpenAI/Gemini pass a model STRING to `Agent`, which pydantic-ai builds + validates internally ŌĆö rebar has no object to introspect there) and for `model_override` (a test double). So the check bounds the path rebar actually owns without false-positiving on provider-string paths. CACHE: a module-level `set()` `_TOOL_CAPABILITY_CHECKED` keyed by the resolved model string ŌĆö the check runs ONCE per unique model per process (not per call), so a hot loop pays nothing.\n- **Tests ŌĆö tools actually offered.** rebar builds the agent's tools as `pai_tools.filesystem_tools(cfg.repo_path)` (callables `read_file`, `list_directory`, `search_files`) + `pai_tools.rebar_tools(cfg.repo_path, allow_comment=ŌĆ”)` (`show_ticket`, and `comment_ticket` when allowed). A test asserts these builders return callables whose `__name__`s are exactly the expected set (so a #5177 hook-returns-None regression that strips a tool is caught).\n- **Tests ŌĆö `usage_limits` on `run*`, not the constructor.** A spy on `Agent`/`run_sync` asserts (a) `run_sync` IS called with `usage_limits=`, and (b) the `Agent(...)` constructor kwargs do NOT include `usage_limits` (the #1987 mis-placement). Confirmed: `Agent.run_sync` accepts `usage_limits`; the constructor does not honor it.\n- **Usage-plausibility telemetry WARNING (never a block).** After a successful run, if `_extract_usage` reports BOTH `input_tokens == 0` AND `output_tokens == 0` while the run produced a non-empty result, log a WARNING (`llm usage looks zeroed/implausible ŌĆ”`) ŌĆö an observability signal for the #5360 zeroed-adapter cluster. It NEVER blocks a gate (usage is observability, not load-bearing); a genuinely tiny run is at worst a benign warning.\n\n## Scope\n- Tests + the construction-time capability check + the telemetry warning. NO per-call runtime blocking for these invariants.\n- NOT in scope: changing the tool surface or provider adapters themselves; a per-call usage assertion.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] Test: `pai_tools.filesystem_tools`/`rebar_tools` offer exactly the expected tool names ŌĆö fails if a tool is stripped (`test_expected_tools_offered`).\n- [ ] Test: `run_sync` is called with `usage_limits=` and the `Agent(...)` constructor is NOT ŌĆö fails on the #1987 mis-placement (`test_usage_limits_on_run_not_constructor`).\n- [ ] Construction-time check: a model OBJECT with `profile.supports_tools == False` used for a tool-using op raises `LLMConfigError`; a string-model path is a NO-OP (test asserts no raise); the check is cached (invoked once per model string, asserted by a spy) ŌĆö `test_capability_check_fails_fast`, `test_capability_check_noop_for_string_model`, `test_capability_check_cached`.\n- [ ] Usage-plausibility emits a WARNING (asserted via caplog) on an all-zero-usage successful run and NEVER blocks (`test_usage_plausibility_warns_never_blocks`).\n- [ ] `make test`/`make lint`/`make typecheck` green.\n\nFiles: `src/rebar/llm/runner.py` (the cached construction-time capability check + the usage-plausibility warning), `tests/unit/test_agent_build_invariants.py` (new).\n\n## Verified library behavior (experiment log ŌĆö pydantic-ai 1.107.0, offline)\nACTUAL captured output (no billable call):\n```\nmodel.profile.supports_tools == True            (the CONCRETE tool-calling capability signal the check reads)\nmodel.profile also exposes: supports_json_schema_output, supports_json_object_output, supports_thinking, ...\nAgent.__init__ has tools/toolsets: True         (tools offered via the constructor; introspectable)\nAgent.run_sync accepts usage_limits: True       (#1987: usage_limits belongs on run*, NOT Agent(...))\nrebar tool builders: pai_tools.filesystem_tools -> [read_file, list_directory, search_files];\n                     pai_tools.rebar_tools -> [show_ticket, (comment_ticket when allow_comment)]\n_extract_usage returns a dict with input_tokens/output_tokens (both 0 => the zeroed-adapter signal)\n```\nThese are pydantic-ai LIBRARY symbols (`model.profile.supports_tools` etc.), not rebar symbols\n(bug succinct-formable-kite: a code-grounding pass must not read repo-absence as non-existence).\n"}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1783666671597374001,"uuid":"1bbde068-1af3-441d-be87-dfdf0d817605"}